Comments: Few macroinvertebrates noted at first netting.  Majority of Netspinner Caddisflies found at 4th (upstream) netting location.  At this location, we also netted 1 minnow and 1 Dusky Salamander.  There was one pocket about 5 inches in diameter of an orange foamy substance floating along the stream edge.
Describe the Amount and Type of Litter: There was one piece of broken brown glass in the stream.  There was one piece of plastic candy bar wrapper and one plastic sandwich baggie recovered from the edge of the stream.
Indicate Current and Potential Threats: This stream is near the end of restoration.  I think it will take time to recover.  Potential threats could be how local neighbors or park visitors treat the stream.
